Takes an RGB or ARGB image and sets it as the background. The width and height of the image must be the same size as the sketch. Use image.resize(width, height) to make short work of such a task. <p/> Note that even if the image is set as RGB, the high 8 bits of each pixel should be set opaque (0xFF000000), because the image data will be copied directly to the screen, and non-opaque background images may have strange behavior. Using image.filter(OPAQUE) will handle this easily. <p/> When using 3D, this will also clear the zbuffer (if it exists).
